<body>
   <div class="contain">
    <div class="top-section">
    <h1> How to became a a fashion designer after completing your class 10th</h1>
    <p>
        To become a fashion designer, you must complete your class 10th education or equivalent. After that, you can enroll in a fashion design program.

    </p>
    </div> 
     <div class="timeline">
        <div class="line"></div>
        <div class="section">
            <div class="bead"></div>
            <div class="content">
                <h2>Choose a fashion design program</h2>
                <p>
                    Look for a fashion design program that offers a comprehensive curriculum covering design, pattern-making, sewing, textiles, and other relevant subjects. You can enroll in a diploma or degree program in fashion design at a fashion school or university.

                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <div class="bead"></div>
            <div class="content">
              <h2> Develop your skills
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Fashion design requires creativity, an eye for detail, and excellent drawing and design skills. Practice drawing, sketching, and designing garments and accessories to develop your skills. You can also learn about fabrics, colors, and patterns by visiting fabric stores and attending fashion shows.


                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <div class="bead"></div>
            <div class="content">
                <h2>Gain experience</h2>
                
                <p>
                    Experience is essential to becoming a successful fashion designer. You can start by working as an assistant to a professional fashion designer or in a fashion design studio. This will give you valuable experience and help you learn about different styles and techniques.


                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <div class="bead"></div>
            <div class="content">
                <h2>Build a portfolio:
                </h2>
                <p>
                    A portfolio is a collection of your best work that showcases your design skills and creativity. Create a portfolio of your designs and sketches, including any pieces you have created during your studies or work experience. Your portfolio will help you get noticed by potential employers or clients.


                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <div class="bead"></div>
            <div class="content">
                <h2>
                    Network
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Attend fashion shows, industry events, and workshops to meet other fashion designers, industry professionals, and potential clients. Networking can help you gain exposure, build relationships, and learn about job or business opportunities.

                </p>
            </div>
        </div><div class="section">
            <div class="bead"></div>
            <div class="content">
                <h2>Chef as a profession
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Becoming a fashion designer requires hard work, dedication, and a passion for fashion. With the right training, skills, and experience, you can succeed in this field.

                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
      
     </div>
   </div>
